result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason D. West was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Carry Concealed Weapon, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.23(2).
  • Carry Concealed Weapon, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.23(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jason D. West in court, in custody with attorney Leah Selmek.  James T. Sempf appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called @ 1:44 p.m. Appearances made. Matter before the Court for plea and sentencing hearing. Record by Atty. Selmek as to agreement of the parties. REsponse by the State. Court goes over maximum penalties/elements and deportation warnings. Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant who responds to Court's questions. Atty. responds to Court's questions regarding plea. 
Defendant pleads GUILTY to counts #1 & #2  Counts #3 & #4 are dismissed and read-in. Court finds pleas to be knowing, voluntary, and intelligent and finds defendant guilty. 
The defendant does not wish to make a statement to the Court. 
Court adopts agreed upon sentence - **SEE ATTACHED PLEA AGREEMENT.**
Court in recess.

Defendant Jason D. West in court, in custody by video with attorney Leah Selmek.  Vivien L. TenHaken appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called @ 8:36 a.m. Appearances made. Matter before the Court for status hearing and motion to modify bond. Record by the Court as to any changes in circumstances that would warrant amendment. Response by Atty. Selmek who responds to further questions of the court. Objection to any bond modification by the State. Court asks how much cash defendant could post. Response by Attorney Selmek. Based upon the record and review of the risk assessment, Court denies request to modify bond.
Record by Atty. Selmek as status. Response by Defendant that he will accept the offer if it is probation. Asks for plea and sentencing tomorrow @ 8:30 a.m. Court sets as requested.

Defendant Jason D. West in court, in custody by video with attorney Jenna Proudfit for Leah Selmek.  James T. Sempf appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called @ 8:59 a.m. Appearances made. Matter before the Court for adjourned initial appearance. Atty. Proudfit goes over charges/penalties and enters not guilty plea on behalf of defendant. Court sets out for status hearing in about 60 days. Court in recess.  Status conference scheduled for March 7, 2022 at 08:30 am.
